The paper discusses the eXplainable AI (XAI) problem and proposes a solution using twin systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the twinning between Artificial Neural Networks (ANN) and Case Based Reasoning (CBR) systems, which are both subfields of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Reasoning (cs.CE), respectively. The paper also discusses the importance of interpretability for users (cs.HC) and the use of explanatory cases (cs.IR) to improve the interpretability of the twin system approach.
